  "texts": [
    "By recognizing key entities, the summary can focus on the most relevant information.",
    "(i) Entity Linking and Disambiguation: NER can be used to link named entities in text to their corresponding entries in a knowledge base such as Wikipedia.",
    "This helps disambiguate entities with multiple meanings and provides additional information about them.",
    "Motivation and contributionsNER is used to extract reference data, such as names of persons, institutions, and organizations, from unstructured legal texts in order to build the framework for the development of a structured database, element extraction, and other tasks.",
    "The goal of this survey is to provide a single architecture capable of handling a variety of NLP tasks, including POS tagging, Chunking, Named Entity Recognition [8], [40], [49], [46], and Semantic role labeling."
  ],
